CEO (Chief Executive Officer)
Provides overall vision, strategy, and leadership for the organization.
In BPR: Champions radical process redesign, ensures alignment with organizational goals, and drives commitment across teams.
COO (Chief Operating Officer)
Manages day-to-day operations and ensures processes run smoothly.
In BPR: Identifies inefficiencies, oversees process reengineering, and implements redesigned workflows to improve operational efficiency.
CFO (Chief Financial Officer)
Oversees financial planning, budgeting, and resource allocation.
In BPR: Evaluates cost implications of process changes, allocates resources for redesign initiatives, and measures financial impact of improved processes.
CIO (Chief Information Officer)
Oversees IT strategy, systems, and technology infrastructure.
In BPR: Ensures technology enables new, efficient processes.
CTO (Chief Technology Officer)
Focuses on technology development, innovation, and product engineering.
In BPR: Introduces tools or platforms that support redesigned processes.
CHRO / CPO (Chief Human Resources / People Officer)
Manages talent, recruitment, training, and organizational culture.
In BPR: Aligns workforce skills with new process requirements and manages change.
CMO (Chief Marketing Officer)
Responsible for marketing strategy, branding, and customer engagement.
In BPR: Provides input to redesign processes that affect customer experience.
CLO (Chief Legal Officer) / General Counsel
Oversees legal compliance, risk management, and contracts.
In BPR: Ensures redesigned processes comply with regulations.